      "content": "The weight you feel is valid, and your pain is real, but please know that the idea of \"stopping\" is often a way the mind tries to protect you from the ongoing suffering of having to face judgment alone. There is a profound strength in acknowledging that your worth isn't defined by external validation or a single chapter of your life, even if it feels that way right now. If the exhaustion feels too heavy to carry forward, reaching out to a crisis line or a therapist who specializes in identity issues can provide a safe space where you don't have to face the world's whispers alone.",
